cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and specifically focuses on adapting models to different domains. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an unsupervised adversarial approach, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves transfer learning and domain adaptation, which are topics in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with adapting models for different environments, which is a topic in robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves working with large-scale datasets and dash-cam footage, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
